Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.lexer.token.TokenInputStream.actual()
    Only use, if you need a complete Token. Use TokenInputStream.actualType(), TokenInputStream.actualStart(), TokenInputStream.actualEnd(), TokenInputStream.actualValue() & TokenInputStream.actualHasValue() instead, if you just need one of these!
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.interpreter.values.Function.call(FunctionCallNode, Scope)
    Moved to Function.invoke(FunctionCallNode, Scope). Will be removed in the future
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.lexer.token.TokenInputStream.get(int)
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.lexer.token.TokenInputStream.getStart(int)
    Avoid using this method and use TokenInputStream.peekStart(), TokenInputStream.actualStart() instead. This method is fully functional, but it uses TokenInputStream.getValue(int), which has to loop over the complete TokenInputStream.tokens array again up to the given token position
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.lexer.token.TokenInputStream.getValue(int)
    This method is fully working, but it will decrease the performance of the program, because it has to loop over all the TokenInputStream.tokens again to find the value's index that should be returned
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.lexer.token.TokenInputStream.next()
    If you don't need a Token, it is advised to use TokenInputStream.nextType() & TokenInputStream.nextValue()
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.lexer.token.TokenInputStream.peek()
    Only use, if you need a complete Token. Use TokenInputStream.peekType(), TokenInputStream.peekStart(), TokenInputStream.peekEnd(), TokenInputStream.peekValue() & TokenInputStream.peekHasValue() instead, if you just need one of these!
    com.github.nsc.de.shake.generators.java.nodes.JavaNode.toString()
    WARNING: To generate java-code use JavaNode.toString(String, String)
